longBusinessSummary: Zonte Metals Inc., a junior exploration company, acquires and explores for mineral properties in Canada. It explores for gold, copper, and silver deposits. The company holds 100% interests in the Wings Point project that consists of seven mineral exploration licenses covering 344 claims covering an area of 8,600 hectares located in the Province of Newfoundland and Labrador; and McConnells Jest project, which consists of 172 claims covering an area of approximately 3,371 hectares located in the Yukon Territory. It also holds a 100% interest in the Cross Hills project that comprises 486 claims covering an area of 12,150 hectares located in the island portion of Newfoundland and Labrador. The company was formerly known as Empire Capital Corp. and changed its name to Zonte Metals Inc. in July 2011. Zonte Metals Inc. was incorporated in 2009 and is headquartered in Halifax, Canada.
